The paper discusses a routing protocol for mobile ad hoc networks, which is a topic related to network infrastructure and communication. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves the use of coding to improve delivery ratio, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of periodic exchange of messages and on-demand routing, which are related to distributed computing (cs.DC) and distributed systems (cs.DS). Finally, the paper involves the use of multiple paths and automatic route recovery, which are related to robotics (cs.RO) as well.
